bilingual.source: Which would you most like to do?
Which would you most like to try?

list.abstract: MOST----Media Oriented System Transport。MOST 系统是利用光导纤维作为信息传导媒介，进行数字信号的传输。首先各控制元件将电磁脉冲信号转化为光脉冲信号，传送到光纤上，而后相应的接收电脑又将光脉冲信号转换回电磁脉冲信号，从而完成相应的控制功能。由于MOST 系统的高传输速率，因此它可以做到只用两根光纤即可同时传递多路信号。
most是一个英语单词，可以用作形容词、副词和名词，可以翻译为很、几乎，等等。

yingyinNormal.en: You know what offends me most?

yingyinNormal.en: The most dangerous thing can be a snake.

yingyinNormal.en: The most important discovery of my life.

yingyinNormal.en: Ghost of the Future. I fear you most of all.

yingyinNormal.en: That's the most romantic thing I've ever heard.

yingyinNormal.en: We are having the most perfect summer ever.

yingyinNormal.en: But most importantly, dedication to this company.

yingyinNormal.en: Why? That is the question people ask me most.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么？这是大家最常问我的问题。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, this is the most romantic disease I've ever had.

yingyinNormal.en: Isn't it the most beautiful thing you've ever seen?

yingyinNormal.en: And the most enjoyable. Phoebe, say something.

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, beefaroni. I think I'll miss you most of all.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，牛肉通心粉，我最怀念的就会是你了。

yingyinNormal.en: Hey, hey. Who'd you miss the most? Monica. Gotcha.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嘿, 你最想念谁呢？ 莫妮卡。知道了。

yingyinNormal.en: Sweet Sixteen. Arbor Day! No, most important first.
yingyinNormal.zh: 甜蜜的16岁。植树节！不，先说最重要的。

yingyinNormal.en: It's a supersonic. The most advanced plane ever built.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这是超音速飞机，有史以来最先进的飞机。

yingyinNormal.en: And most importantly, you've experienced the power of community.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还有最重要的，你们体会到了团结的力量。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: And most prominently, you've got your average-joes-who-you-would never-know-are-gay gays.
yingyinNormal.zh: 最重要的是，有你这种"绝对看不出来是基佬"类型的基佬。

yingyinNormal.en: How much time? An hour. Two, at most.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有多少时间? 一小时，最多两小时。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adv. 几乎全部地；多半；通常；一般

word_family.mean: det. & pro. 最大的；最高程度的；大多数的；几乎全部的；（many和much的最高级）

examination_example.sentence: There is a gap in working-class jobs, but the workers who need those jobs <highlight>most</highlight> aren't equipped to do them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 工人阶级的工作存在差距，但最需要这些工作的工人却没有能力做这些工作。

examination_example.sentence: But Mauna Kea is also home to some of the world's <highlight>most</highlight> powerful telescopes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但莫纳克亚山也是世界上一些最强大望远镜的所在地。

examination_example.sentence: But perhaps the <highlight>most</highlight> significant reason is that the issue has always been so politically charged.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但或许最重要的原因是，这个问题一直都带有政治色彩。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Most</highlight> land is used for meat and dairy production.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数土地用于肉类和奶制品生产。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Most</highlight> people are not comfortable holding eye contact with strangers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数人都觉得和陌生人有眼神交流不舒服。

examination_example.sentence: First, <highlight>most</highlight> researchers would accept such a prize if they were offered one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首先，如果能得到这样的奖励，大多数研究人员都会接受。

sense_info_list.en: the largest in number or amount

word_usage.usage: most作副词时，也可修饰另一个副词，如果后面只接副词时不用加the，如：This reason is mentioned most frequently，或者说 This is the most frequently mentioned reason.

most作代词时，常与介系of连用，“most+of+名词”用作主语时，其谓语动词要根据后面的名词来决定单复数形式，如：
Most of her books were stolen. 她的大部分书都被偷了。
Most of the money was spent. 大部分钱都花掉了。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Most</highlight> people feel nervous sitting across from a hiring manager, answering questions that effectively open themselves up for judgment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数人坐在招聘经理的对面，回答让自己接受评判的问题时会感到紧张。

examination_example.sentence: A recent analysis found that <highlight>most</highlight> research mischaracterizes the relationship between music and skills enhancement.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最近的一项分析发现，大多数研究错误地描述了音乐和技能提高之间的关系。

examination_example.sentence: But here's a crucial point <highlight>most</highlight> people miss: People also repeat bad ideas when they complain about them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是这里有一个大多数人都忽略的关键点:当人们抱怨不好的想法时，他们也会重复这些想法。

sense_info_list.zh: 最的; 最大的; 相当地

examination_example.sentence: However, research agendas need to be focused on the needs of the poorest and <highlight>most</highlight> resource-limited countries.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，研究议程需要集中于最贫穷和资源最有限的国家的需求。

examination_example.sentence: Talk to anyone who's a generation not too older and they would <highlight>most</highlight> likely comment that children are more spoiled these days.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 和任何一个年纪不大的人交谈，他们很可能会说现在的孩子更被宠坏了。

examination_example.sentence: Reason and thought were <highlight>most</highlight> valued in this garden—all derived from the project of the Enlightenment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这座花园里，理性和思想最受重视——一切都源于启蒙运动。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

derivative_info_list.mean: adv. 几乎全部地；多半；通常；一般

word_family.mean: det. & pro. 最大的；最高程度的；大多数的；几乎全部的；（many和much的最高级）

examination_example.sentence: However, <highlight>most</highlight> people don't regard pronunciation as a very important part of communication skills.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，大多数人并不认为发音是沟通技巧中非常重要的一部分。

examination_example.sentence: One reason is that <highlight>most</highlight> people are not even aware of their mispronunciations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个原因是大多数人甚至没有意识到他们的发音错误。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Most</highlight> museums also welcome school groups and arrange special activities for children.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数博物馆也欢迎学校团体，并为孩子们安排特别的活动。

examination_example.sentence: That was the period of time I enjoyed <highlight>most</highlight> in Toronto.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 那是我在多伦多最开心的一段时间。

examination_example.sentence: But the <highlight>most</highlight> important information I want to give you now is about safety.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是我现在想给你的最重要的信息是关于安全的。

examination_example.sentence: This tour transports you back in time to one of San Francisco's <highlight>most</highlight> fantastic periods, the 1950s!
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这次旅行带你回到旧金山最精彩的时期之一，20世纪50年代！

word_usage.usage:
形容词最高级前加不定冠词，表示“非常，很”，相当于very；加定冠词则表示“最”：
This is a most interesting book but it is not the most interesting book I have ever read.
这是一本非常有趣的书，但不是我看过的最有趣的书。

数据源自2018-2021年4年间全国各省市中考试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2018-2021年全国重点省市中考试卷，包括听力、阅读、完形、单选、填空、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2018-2021年4年间全国各省市中考试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

derivative_info_list.mean: adv. 几乎全部地；多半；通常；一般

word_family.mean: det. & pro. 最大的；最高程度的；大多数的；几乎全部的；（many和much的最高级）

examination_example.sentence: conversation <highlight>most</highlight> probably take place?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对话最有可能发生？

examination_example.sentence: She said there are 32 steps to make a pair, but the <highlight>most</highlight> important step is making the soles.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她说制作一双鞋需要32个步骤，但最重要的一步是制作鞋底。

examination_example.sentence: China is now the third <highlight>most</highlight> popular country for international students, behind the United States and the United Kingdom.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 中国现在是第三个最受国际学生欢迎的国家，仅次于美国和英国。

sense_info_list.zh: 大部分的; 大多数的

examination_example.sentence: How old are <highlight>most</highlight> children when they have learned about 50 words?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数孩子学了大约50个单词，他们多大了？

examination_example.sentence: But <highlight>most</highlight> people probably won’t want to see the insects they eat.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但大多数人可能不想看到他们吃的昆虫。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Most</highlight> people, generally speaking, are ready to smile back when they are smiled at.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一般来说，大多数人在被别人微笑时都会报以微笑。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Most</highlight> of us are not extreme athletes or explorers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们大多数人都不是极限运动员或探险家。

examination_example.sentence: An old lady whose life was worse than <highlight>most</highlight> of us still thought others.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一位生活比我们大多数人都糟糕的老太太仍然在想其他人。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Most</highlight> of the eggs we eat come from hens.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们吃的大多数鸡蛋来自母鸡。

word_usage.usage: most不仅是many，much的最高级，还可以用在部分双音节或多音节的形容词或副词前协助构成最高级。如most beautiful等。
